                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d526">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13980: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bucknell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-29T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 29, 1938—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 29—8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>255. My telegram No. 245, September 28, 3 p.m. The Council in secret session this
                    afternoon decided to submit a report instead of a resolution to the Council
                    tomorrow in regard to the Chinese appeal under article 17. The report is in
                    general in accordance with my telegram referred to above but is considerably
                    “watered down”. Please instruct whether Department desires full text<note n="67"
                        xml:id="d526fn67">The Department assumed publication of text in the
                        press.</note> consisting of about 500 words by telegraph when adopted
                    tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucknell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
